Like fingerprints in humans, they can be used to identify each individual.\nPlease take screenshots only of the two left sides of the first leopard at 0:02 and the second leopard at 5:09 and compare the flanks and the back thighs: The design of the rosettes is perfectly identical: This is proof that it is the same leopard and that he was not injured when passing through the mirror.\nThank you for watching this other video in which I prove with the rosette pattern that a leopard mother filmed 3 years later with a different child is indeed the same mother https://youtu.be/D-Aar9R5jbY\nTo avoid any possible injury, the new mirror has been reinforced on his back by a thick sheet of plywood clamped with him in the metal frame.\nWatch the following videos to see how the new mirrors are made and see how resistant they are to shocks:\nhttps://youtu.be/NdD1on4H9ss\nhttps://youtu.be/9jxwVgul_lM\nAfter watching each video on my YouTube channel, don't forget to click on the \"show more\" option, I attach a description with more information to each of my 150 published videos https://www.youtube.com/XHB06400CANNES/videos"}}, "contentDetails": {"duration": "PT5M42S", "dimension": "2d", "definition": "hd", "caption": "false", "licensedContent": true, "contentRating": {}, "projection": "rectangular"}, "status": {"uploadStatus": "processed", "privacyStatus": "public", "license": "youtube", "embeddable": true, "publicStatsViewable": true, "madeForKids": false}, "statistics": {"viewCount": "46352", "likeCount": "463", "favoriteCount": "0", "commentCount": "176"}, "player": {"embedHtml": "<iframe width=\"480\" height=\"270\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/488VUus49eE\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; Besicosssss con sabor a gratitud y todo mi cari\u00f1o!!!\r\nEL CORAZON MAS HERMOSO\r\n\r\nUn d\u00eda un hombre joven se situ\u00f3 en el centro de un poblado y proclam\u00f3 que \u00e9l pose\u00eda el coraz\u00f3n m\u00e1s hermoso de toda la comarca. \r\nUna gran multitud se congreg\u00f3 a su alrededor y todos admiraron y confirmaron que su coraz\u00f3n era perfecto, pues no se observaban en \u00e9l ni m\u00e1culas ni rasgu\u00f1os. S\u00ed, coincidieron todos que era el coraz\u00f3n m\u00e1s hermoso que hubieran visto. \r\nAl verse admirado el joven se sinti\u00f3 m\u00e1s orgulloso a\u00fan, y con mayor fervor asegur\u00f3 poseer el coraz\u00f3n m\u00e1s hermoso de todo el vasto lugar. \r\nDe pronto un anciano se acerc\u00f3 y dijo: \"\u00bfPorqu\u00e9 dices eso, si tu coraz\u00f3n no es ni tan, aproximadamente, tan hermoso como el m\u00edo? \r\nSorprendidos la multitud y el joven miraron el coraz\u00f3n del viejo y vieron que, si bien lat\u00eda vigorosamente, \u00e9ste estaba cubierto de cicatrices y hasta hab\u00eda zonas donde faltaban trozos y \u00e9stos hab\u00edan sido reemplazados por otros que no encastraban perfectamente en el lugar, pues se ve\u00edan bordes y aristas irregulares en su derredor. \r\nEs m\u00e1s, hab\u00eda lugares con huecos, donde faltaban trozos profundos. \r\nLa mirada de la gente se sobrecogi\u00f3 \"\u00bfC\u00f3mo puede \u00e9l decir que su coraz\u00f3n es m\u00e1s hermoso?\", pensaron ... \r\nEl joven contempl\u00f3 el coraz\u00f3n del anciano y al ver su estado desgarbado, se ech\u00f3 a re\u00edr. \"Debes estar bromeando,\" dijo. \"Compara tu coraz\u00f3n con el m\u00edo... el m\u00edo es perfecto. En cambio el tuyo es un conjunto de cicatrices y dolor.\" \r\n\"Es cierto,\" dijo el anciano, \"tu coraz\u00f3n luce perfecto, pero yo jam\u00e1s me involucrar\u00eda contigo\"... \r\nMira, cada cicatriz representa una persona a la cual entregu\u00e9 todo mi amor. Arranqu\u00e9 trozos de mi coraz\u00f3n para entreg\u00e1rselos a cada uno de aquellos que he amado. \r\nMuchos a su vez, me han obsequiado un trozo del suyo, que he colocado en el lugar que qued\u00f3 abierto. Como las piezas no eran iguales, quedaron los bordes por los cuales me alegro, porque al poseerlos me recuerdan el amor que hemos compartido.\" \r\n\"Hubo oportunidades, en las cuales entregu\u00e9 un trozo de mi coraz\u00f3n a alguien, pero esa persona no me ofreci\u00f3 un poco del suyo a \r\ncambio. De ah\u00ed quedaron los huecos. \r\nDar amor es arriesgar, pero a pesar del dolor que esas heridas me producen al haber quedado abiertas, me recuerdan que los sigo amando y alimentan la esperanza, que alg\u00fan d\u00eda, quiz\u00e1s, regresen y llenen el vac\u00edo que han dejado en mi coraz\u00f3n.\" \r\n\u00bfComprendes ahora lo que es verdaderamente hermoso?\" \r\nEl joven permaneci\u00f3 en silencio, l\u00e1grimas corr\u00edan por sus mejillas. \r\nSe acerc\u00f3 al anciano, arranc\u00f3 un trozo de su hermoso y joven coraz\u00f3n y se lo ofreci\u00f3. \r\nEl anciano lo recibi\u00f3 y lo coloc\u00f3 en su coraz\u00f3n, luego a su vez arranc\u00f3 un trozo del suyo ya viejo y maltrecho y con \u00e9l tap\u00f3 la herida abierta del joven. \r\nLa pieza se amold\u00f3, pero no a la perfecci\u00f3n. Al no haber sido id\u00e9nticos los trozos, se notaban los bordes. \r\nEl joven mir\u00f3 su coraz\u00f3n que ya no era perfecto, pero luc\u00eda mucho m\u00e1s hermoso que antes, porque el amor del anciano flu\u00eda en su interior. \r\n\u00a1Desde aqu\u00ed puedo ver lo hermoso que es tu coraz\u00f3n! \r\n\u00a1Que tengais un lindo d\u00eda! Otters have a long muscular tail, short stout legs and thick oiled fur. Small rounded ears and nostrils close when the otter is underwater. In Florida, river otters weigh 11 to 31 lbs. and males are larger than females.\nRiver otters forage alone or in pairs. They are active during the day and at night, hunting in streams, rivers and ponds for fish, crayfish and turtles. Otters have a high metabolic rate, an adaptation for living in an aquatic environment where body heat is rapidly lost. They need to eat 15% of their body weight a day. Although otters always remain in or near the water, they spend their inactive time in burrows dug into riverbanks or at other rest sites on land. Dens are located in shelters dug by other animals or natural hollows.\nOtters breed once a year and in Florida mating occurs in fall and winter. Though the embryos develop for about 8 weeks. Litters usually consist of 2-4 kits, which are born fully furred. The young open their eyes after a month and are weaned at three months. They travel and feed with their mother until they are about a year old. Otters have a long muscular tail, short stout legs and thick oiled fur. Small rounded ears and nostrils close when the otter is underwater. In Florida, river otters weigh 11 to 31 lbs. and males are larger than females.\nRiver otters forage alone or in pairs. They are active during the day and at night, hunting in streams, rivers and ponds for fish, crayfish and turtles. Otters have a high metabolic rate, an adaptation for living in an aquatic environment where body heat is rapidly lost. They need to eat 15% of their body weight a day. Although otters always remain in or near the water, they spend their inactive time in burrows dug into riverbanks or at other rest sites on land. Dens are located in shelters dug by other animals or natural hollows.\nOtters breed once a year and in Florida mating occurs in fall and winter. Though the embryos develop for about 8 weeks. Litters usually consist of 2-4 kits, which are born fully furred. The young open their eyes after a month and are weaned at three months. They travel and feed with their mother until they are about a year old. The reservere is an integral part of the spectacular Serengeti-Mara Ecosystem, home of the Great Migration and Africa's greatest wildlife populations. Since 2006 Singita manages the property and began the task of generating, via low impact tourism, the funds necessary to ensure the long-term sustainability of the reserve through conservation and community partnerships.\n\nYou will hopefully get a general idea of this wonderful region, the top-notch hospitality and the connectivity to African wildlife as well as Singita's choice of luxury accomodation: Singita Sasakwa Lodge, Singita Sabora Tented Camp, Singita Faru Faru Lodge, Singita Serengeti House, Singita Explore (all within the Singita Grumeti Reserve in Tanzania).\n\nSpanning over 350,000 acres of untouched wilderness, Singita Grumeti is definitely amongst the best wildlife spots on the African continent. Want to know our favourite lodge of Singita Grumeti? Well, it's Singita Faru Faru! Built on a gently sloping hill, this riverine lodge, positioned on the renowned migratory route, is a place where you can quite literally expect the unexpected. Informal, unconventional and surprising at every turn, Singita Faru Faru Lodge is a mix of contemporary, organic style and the quirky practicality of a traditional botanist\u2019s camp. With such close proximity to the river and plains, guests have the unique opportunity to experience a very close connection with the wilderness.\n\nBegleitet uns auf eine Reise hinein in das Safari-Paradies Singita Grumeti, ein exklusives Reservat an der Grenze der Serengti im n\u00f6rdlichen Tansania. 5 Sterne reichen nicht, um die au\u00dfergew\u00f6hnliche Qualit\u00e4t, das Lebensgef\u00fchl und den Grad an unpr\u00e4tenti\u00f6sen Luxus zu beschreiben, der jeder der Singita Lodges innewohnt.
